thread.title: CORRECTED-Australia's Wesfarmers says Q3 supermarket sales up 1.3 pct

author: Reuters Editorial
title: CORRECTED-Australia's Wesfarmers says Q3 supermarket sales up 1.3 pct
text:
(Corrects to supermarket sales in headline and lead, and corrects period for sales figure in paragraph 2)
April 26 (Reuters) - Australiaâ€™s Wesfarmers Ltd said on Thursday its third-quarter comparable supermarket store sales rose 1.3 percent, after adjustments for holidays, though Bunnings UK same-store sales slumped 15.4 percent due to poor weather in March.
The retail-to-resources conglomerate said headline food and liquor sales rose 1.9 percent to A$25.1 billion ($19 billion) for the financial year to March.
$1 = 1.3221 Australian dollars Reporting by Devika Syamnath in Bengaluru; Editing by Stephen Coates
